About Key Skills for Math: Shapes, Numbers, and Measurements
Reinforce number measurement and basic geometry skills with these quick-paced activities. An assessment tool provides you with diagnostic student reports. Students develop basic skills as they:

# name and match plane and three-dimensional shapes
# solve inequalities and make other math statements true
# learn the value of coins by counting coins up to $2.00
# build simple subtraction skills
# understand basic unit measures of time and temperature
